          <text>
                    <body>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
                              <p>With this you will no doubt also receive a letter <del>by</del> of
                                                  <persName>M. Strauss Esq.</persName><lb/> our
                                        Parnass, concerning the affairs of <persName>Mr.
                                                  Henry</persName> and myself. I wrote<lb/> to you
                                        last week on the same subject, but <add>?</add> in the
                                        Occident<lb/> for this month that you rather somewhat
                                        disbelieve my state,<lb/>ment from last year, and fearing
                                        you might perhaps be induced<lb/> to do the same now, I
                                        requested <persName>Mr. Strauss</persName>, to write so
                                        you<lb/> on the same subject himself, as the head of this
                                        congregation. I pray,<lb/> do me the favour of inserting
                                                  <del>the</del> his communication, as your
                                        editorial<lb/> seem to have appeared just in the right time
                                        to favour <persName>Mr. Henry</persName><lb/> and so injure
                                        me. I know full well, that your intention is good,<lb/> and
                                        that you <sic>allways</sic> strife to do justice to all and
                                        every one with<lb/>in the influence of your
                                                  <sic>correspondenze</sic> and this knowledge
                                        gives<lb/> me the hope—nay—the certainty, that you will
                                        insert <persName>Mr. Strauss</persName><lb/> letter, just as
                                        it reads, in your next months Occident and if<lb/> you
                                        should think proper to be paid for, I will cheerfully
                                        pay<lb/> myself for the insertion of the same. At the same
                                        time you<lb/> are at perfect liberty to lay by my
                                        communication on that subject,<lb/> provided you will be
                                        kind enough to insert the letter of <persName>Mr.
                                                  Strauss</persName>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">Yours</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">most respectfully</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">
                                        <persName role="author">B H. Gotthelf</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p><placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName>
                                        <date>Aug. 10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1851</date>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <add>יום א י"א אב תר"י לפק</add>
                              </p>
